        "text": " Samavaya\u2014or coexistence is defined as that inseparable relationship which subsists between earth and other proto-elements and their qualities. This relationship is eternal; for, wherever the substance exists the coexistent quality is never absent."
    },
    {
        "verse_id": "50\u00bd",
        "text": " That which is the substratum of action and qualities and is the ' coexistent cause is \u2018substance.\u2019"
    },
    {
        "verse_id": "51",
        "text": " \u2018Quality\u2019 is the coexistent and inactive cause."
    },
    {
        "verse_id": "52",
        "text": " \u2018Action,\u2019 which is the cause of conjunction and disjunction, resides in the substance. Action is the performance of what is to be done. It depends on nothing else."
    },
    { "verse_id": "52.1", "text": "Thus has been defined, \u2018Cause\u2019" },
    {
        "verse_id": "53",
        "text": " The action here i.e. in medicine, is establishing \u201cthe equilibrium of the body-elements,\u201d and the procedure of maintaining the equilibrium of the body-elements is the objective of this science."
    },
    {
        "verse_id": "54",
        "text": " The complex of causes with reference to disease\u2014psychic and somatic\u2014is either erroneous, absent or excessive interaction between time, mind, senses and sense-objects."
    },
    {
        "verse_id": "55",
        "text": " The body and that which is called the mind are both considered to be the abodes of disease, likewise of well-being; the cause of well-being is their harmonious or concordant interaction."
    },
    {
        "verse_id": "56",
        "text": " The spirit, which is changeless and transcendental, becomes the cause of consciousness when united with the mind, sense-objects and the senses. It is the eternal witness observing actions."
    },
    {
        "verse_id": "57",
        "text": " Vata, pitta and kapha are said to be the complex of pathogenic factors in the body; and passion and delusion are considered to be the complex of pathogenic factors of the mind."
    },
    {
        "verse_id": "58",
        "text": " The former type of morbidity is quieted by medications, divine and physical and the latter by spiritual Knowledge, philosophy, fortitude, remembrance and concentration."
    },
    {
        "verse_id": "59",
        "text": " The Vata is dry, cold, light, subtle, unstable, clear and rough; it is quieted by substances of the antagonistic qualities."
    },
    {
        "verse_id": "60",
        "text": " The Pitta is slightly unctuous, hot, acute, fluid, acid, mobile and pungent; it is readily quieted by substances of the antagonistic qualities."
    },
    {
        "verse_id": "61",
        "text": " The Kapha is heavy, cold, soft, unctuous, sweet, stable and viscid; it is quieted by substances of the antagonistic qualities."
    },
    {
        "verse_id": "62-62\u00bd",
        "text": " The disorders, classed as curable, disappear when treated with therapeutic agents of the antagonistic qualities, with due consideration to climate, dosage and time."
    },
    {
        "verse_id": "The treatment of incurable diseases is",
        "text": " however, not contemplated."
    },
    {
        "verse_id": "63",
        "text": " Now, a further description of qualities and actions with reference to individual substances will be given."

},
